---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Nav from "../components/nav.astro";
---

<Layout title="Berk KÖKSAL | Official Biography">
  <Nav />

  <section class="min-h-screen py-28">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto space-y-28">

      <!-- HERO -->
      <header class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-[0.9fr_1.1fr] gap-12 items-center">
        <div>
          <p class="text-accent text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.45em] font-bold mb-5">
            Official Artist Biography
          </p>

          <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-heading font-bold text-maintext mb-6">
            Berk KÖKSAL
          </h1>

          <p class="text-xl text-accent leading-8 mb-8">
            Composer • Guitarist • Music Producer • Software Engineer<br />
            Founder of Neo-Sacred Zikr
          </p>

          <p class="text-subtext text-lg leading-8 max-w-2xl">
            Berk KÖKSAL is a Turkish composer, guitarist, vocalist, songwriter,
            arranger, music producer, mix and mastering engineer, software
            engineer, Computer Science graduate and QUR'AN researcher.
          </p>
        </div>

        <img
          src="/artist/berk-portrait.webp"
          alt="Berk Köksal portrait"
          class="rounded-[2rem] border border-accent/20 shadow-2xl shadow-accent/10"
        />
      </header>

      <!-- ABOUT -->
      <section class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-[0.75fr_1.25fr] gap-12">
        <div>
          <p class="text-accent text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.45em] font-bold mb-4">
            I
          </p>
          <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-heading font-bold text-maintext">
            About
          </h2>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-6 text-subtext text-lg leading-8">
          <p>
            Berk KÖKSAL's musical journey began with guitar performances and home
            studio recordings. Over time, this journey evolved into a wider sound
            world shaped by neoclassical guitars, symphonic choirs, ambient sound
            design, sacred atmospheres, rap vocals, children's choirs, cathedral
            organs, progressive rock and modern production techniques.
          </p>

          <p>
            His work is not centered merely on genre, technique or production.
            At the heart of his music is the desire to glorify <strong class="text-maintext">GOD</strong>.
            For him, music is more than a career: it is a path of submission,
            a call to remembrance and an effort to proclaim belief in the ONE GOD
            through the sounds of the modern age.
          </p>

          <p>
            This artistic direction became the foundation of the musical approach
            he named <strong class="text-maintext">Neo-Sacred Zikr</strong>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- QURAN VERSE -->
      <a
        href="https://qurantft.com"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="block p-10 md:p-14 rounded-[2rem] border border-accent/30 bg-accent/5 hover:bg-accent/10 transition-all text-center"
      >
        <p class="text-accent text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.45em] font-bold mb-5">
          QURAN: THE FINAL TESTAMENT
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-heading font-bold text-maintext leading-tight">
          [87:1] Glorify the name of your Lord, the Most High.
        </h2>

        <p class="mt-6 text-accent text-sm">
          Quran: The Final Testament ↗
        </p>
      </a>

      <!-- MISSION -->
      <section class="rounded-[2rem] border border-accent/20 bg-accent/5 p-10 md:p-14">
        <p class="text-accent text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.45em] font-bold mb-5">
          II · Mission
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-heading font-bold text-maintext mb-8">
          Music as Remembrance
        </h2>

        <div class="space-y-5 text-subtext text-lg leading-8 max-w-4xl">
          <p>
            The reason Berk KÖKSAL began creating zikr music is rooted in his
            QUR'AN-centered understanding of submission: to remember GOD, to
            glorify GOD and to make the beautiful names of GOD heard throughout
            the world.
          </p>

          <p>
            In his works, phrases such as Allah, La ilaha illa Allah,
            Allahu Akbar, Subhan Allah, Alhamdulillah, Ya Rahman, Ya Rahim,
            Ya Nur and Ya Hannan are not merely words. They become musical
            gestures of remembrance.
          </p>

          <p class="text-maintext font-bold text-2xl leading-9">
            Every repetition is a turning toward GOD. Every choir is an ascent.
            Every guitar is an inner search. Every atmosphere is part of submission.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- BANNER -->
      <section class="relative rounded-[2rem] overflow-hidden border border-accent/20">
        <img
          src="/artist/neo-sacred-zikr-banner-2.webp"
          alt="Neo-Sacred Zikr banner"
          class="w-full h-[360px] md:h-[480px] object-cover opacity-80"
        />

        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-background via-background/65 to-transparent"></div>

        <div class="absolute inset-0 flex items-center p-10 md:p-16">
          <div>
            <p class="text-accent text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.45em] font-bold mb-4">
              Artistic Vision
            </p>

            <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-heading font-bold text-maintext">
              Neo-Sacred Zikr
            </h2>

            <p class="mt-5 max-w-2xl text-subtext text-lg leading-8">
              A sacred sound universe where zikr, sacred music, spiritual music,
              devotional music, symphonic zikr, ambient zikr, sacred rap and
              choral music meet under one purpose: glorifying GOD.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ARTISTIC PHILOSOPHY -->
      <section>
        <p class="text-accent text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.45em] font-bold mb-5">
          III · Artistic Philosophy
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-heading font-bold text-maintext mb-10">
          Genres are tools, not the destination.
        </h2>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
          {[
            "Rock",
            "Metal",
            "Rap",
            "Symphonic Choir",
            "Ambient Zikr",
            "Neoclassical",
            "Sacred Music",
            "Cathedral Organ",
            "Children Choir"
          ].map((item) => (
            <div class="p-7 rounded-2xl border border-accent/20 bg-accent/5">
              <p class="text-accent text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em] mb-3">
                Neo-Sacred Element
              </p>
              <h3 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold text-maintext">
                {item}
              </h3>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>

        <p class="mt-10 text-subtext text-lg leading-8 max-w-4xl">
          Berk KÖKSAL reinterprets the familiar idea of zikr through a contemporary
          musical language. Rock, metal, rap, symphonic forms, church-music
          aesthetics, organ textures, ambient atmospheres, cinematic production
          and modern sound design are all used as instruments to glorify GOD and
          invite the listener to remembrance.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- ONE MAN PRODUCTION -->
      <section class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-[0.8fr_1.2fr] gap-12 items-start">
        <div>
          <p class="text-accent text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.45em] font-bold mb-5">
            IV · Production
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-heading font-bold text-maintext">
            One-Man Production Vision
          </h2>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
          {[
            "Composition",
            "Lyrics",
            "Guitars",
            "Vocals",
            "Recording",
            "MIDI Programming",
            "Orchestration",
            "Sound Design",
            "Mixing",
            "Mastering",
            "Album Artwork",
            "Software Development"
          ].map((item) => (
            <div class="rounded-xl border border-accent/20 bg-accent/5 p-4 text-maintext font-bold">
              {item}
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ALBUMS -->
      <section>
        <p class="text-accent text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.45em] font-bold mb-5">
          V · Albums
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-heading font-bold text-maintext mb-10">
          Albums and Sacred Music Universe
        </h2>

        <div class="space-y-5">
          {[
            ["2024", "Tanrı'nın Hediyesi", "Repentance, purification, forgiveness and turning toward GOD."],
            ["2025", "Zikr Symphony", "Symphonic orchestra, choir, progressive rock, neoclassical metal, organ and zikr structures."],
            ["2026", "Zikr Huu", "A minimal and peaceful album focused on the silent remembrance of the heart."],
            ["2026", "Zikr Nur", "Female vocals, rain atmospheres, ney melodies and ambient sound design."],
            ["2026", "ZIKR ROCK", "Rock and metal transformed into a powerful language of remembrance."],
            ["2026", "Classical Chorus", "Sacred choral aesthetics, liturgical harmonies and cathedral atmosphere."],
            ["2026", "One GOD One Love", "Children's choir, universal light and the message of One GOD, One Love, One Truth."],
            ["2026", "ZIKR RAP", "Spiritual rap, sacred hip-hop and boom bap rhythms dedicated to remembrance."],
            ["2026", "Zikr-i Batın", "A deeply personal album centered on inner zikr and the beautiful names of GOD."]
          ].map(([year, title, description]) => (
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[120px_1fr] gap-4 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-accent/20 bg-accent/5">
              <p class="text-accent font-bold">{year}</p>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold text-maintext mb-2">
                  {title}
                </h3>
                <p class="text-subtext leading-7">{description}</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- QURAN RESEARCH -->
      <section class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-10">
        <div class="p-8 rounded-2xl border border-accent/20 bg-accent/5">
          <p class="text-accent text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.35em] font-bold mb-4">
            QUR'AN Research
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-maintext mb-5">
            Kuransonahit and QUR'AN Study
          </h2>

          <p class="text-subtext leading-8">
            In addition to music, Berk KÖKSAL has worked for many years in
            QUR'AN research and software development. His aim is to encourage
            people to reflect directly on the QUR'AN, verify information and
            think deeply about GOD's message.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-8 rounded-2xl border border-accent/20 bg-accent/5">
          <p class="text-accent text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.35em] font-bold mb-4">
            Software & Education
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-maintext mb-5">
            Computer Science and Certifications
          </h2>

          <p class="text-subtext leading-8">
            Berk KÖKSAL is a Computer Science graduate and software engineer.
            He has completed professional programs in music production,
            Pro Tools, digital marketing, analytics, cloud technologies,
            data science, AI, cybersecurity and software development.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- FINAL -->
      <section class="text-center py-20">
        <p class="text-accent text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.45em] font-bold mb-8">
          Final Statement
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-heading font-bold text-maintext leading-tight max-w-5xl mx-auto">
          Music is not my destination.<br />
          It is my way of glorifying GOD.
        </h2>
      </section>

      <a
        href="https://qurantft.com"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="block p-10 md:p-14 rounded-[2rem] border border-accent/30 bg-accent/5 hover:bg-accent/10 transition-all text-center"
      >
        <p class="text-accent text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.45em] font-bold mb-5">
          QURAN: THE FINAL TESTAMENT
        </p>

        <p class="text-subtext text-sm mb-6">
          Authorized English Version · Translated by Rashad Khalifa
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-heading font-bold text-maintext leading-tight">
          [87:1] Glorify the name of your Lord, the Most High.
        </h2>

        <p class="mt-6 text-accent text-sm">
          Quran: The Final Testament ↗
        </p>
      </a>

    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>